column4: heya, I need some help with ubuntu. I don't know if it's ubuntu specific. Networking in ubuntu doesn't seem to work. Booting into windows is fine(dhcp) is fine. Ubuntu static and dhcp doesn't work
pinging google.com works. nslookup google.com is correct. Trying to connect to googl.com doesn't work.Sticking in the ip address works
- try "telnet www.google.com 80" & see if you get a connection...
you haven't configd a proxy inside ff by mistake?
more likely it's nat on the router
looks that way otherwise they'd block of my ping right?
do you have access lists anywhere on the router? firewall?
well ping IP works, does ping www.yahoo.com work?
Thanks, back in business. Router was trying to be too helpful. Slashdot.org still doesn't resolve though
do any URLs resolve? eg www.yahoo.com? www.slashdot.org ?
All except slashdot.org, i keep getting some doubleclick advertising server. Might be cached
who's good looking? You are ! worked,
k, ff's cache was borked- it happens
